M||tx|---
M||name|er-tracking-shared
M||desc|Shared er tracking standard for all yv ag. Defines structured log format, er classification, HTTP status rules, and no-PII policy. Source of truth referenced by rj, dv, mi, and qn.
M||vers|1.1.0
M||appl|all-tc-ag
M||tx|---
M|Erro|> Ca|`shared/skills/custom/er-tracking/SKILL.md`
M|Erro|tx|> rj's cp at `tc/rj/skills/custom/er-tracking/SKILL.md` is the origin — this shared file mirrors it.
M|Erro|tx|> If they conflict, up rj's file and sync here.
M|Erro|tx|---
M|Stru|Ever|
M|Stru|tx|```ts
M|Stru|tx|if YVONErrorLog {
M|Stru|tp|'route_error' \| 'auth_error' \| 'db_error' \| 'external_api_error' \| 'validation_error'
M|Stru|rt|string          // '/ap/[exact-rt-name]'
M|Stru|meth|'GET' \| 'POST' \| 'PUT' \| 'dl' \| 'PATCH'
M|Stru|mess|string        // us-safe message only — NOT err.message
M|Stru|vent|string   // context for multi-vt debugging, not PII
M|Stru|time|string      // new Date().toISOString()
M|Stru|// N|stack trace, err.message, ap keys, em, name, payment info
M|Stru|tx|}
M|Stru|tx|```
M|Stru|**Im|**
M|Stru|tx|```ts
M|Stru|func|Partial<YVONErrorLog>) {
M|Stru|tx|console.er(JSON.stringify({
M|Stru|tp|er.tp ?? 'route_error',
M|Stru|rt|er.rt,
M|Stru|meth|er.method,
M|Stru|mess|er.message ?? 'An er occurred.',
M|Stru|vent|er.venture_slug ?? 'unknown',
M|Stru|time|new Date().toISOString()
M|Stru|tx|}))
M|Stru|tx|}
M|Stru|tx|```
M|Stru|tx|---
M|Erro|tx|\| er tp \| When to use \| Log level \|
M|Erro|tx|\|-----------\|------------\|-----------\|
M|Erro|tx|\| `validation_error` \| Zod parse failed, bad input \| `console.warn` \|
M|Erro|tx|\| `auth_error` \| getUser() failed, sn expired \| `console.warn` \|
M|Erro|tx|\| `route_error` \| Unexpected er in handler \| `console.er` \|
M|Erro|tx|\| `db_error` \| sb query failed \| `console.er` \|
M|Erro|tx|\| `external_api_error` \| Apify, YouTube, GA4 fl \| `console.warn` \|
M|Erro|tx|`4xx` er → WARN (client fault) · `5xx` er → er (our sy fault)
M|Erro|tx|---
M|HTTP|tx|\| Scenario \| Status \|
M|HTTP|tx|\|----------\|--------\|
M|HTTP|tx|\| Zod validation failed \| `400` \|
M|HTTP|tx|\| Missing or invalid auth \| `401` \|
M|HTTP|tx|\| Authenticated, not authorized \| `403` \|
M|HTTP|tx|\| Resource not found \| `404` \|
M|HTTP|tx|\| Rate limit exceeded \| `429` + `Retry-After` header \|
M|HTTP|tx|\| Unexpected server er \| `500` \|
M|HTTP|| De|5` \|
M|HTTP|**No|** Never return `200` w/ an er body. Never `500` for client input. Never `401` for authorization fl (that is `403`).
M|HTTP|tx|---
M|No-P|**Ne|** em, full names, phone, payment data, sn/auth tk, raw ap keys, IP addresses.
M|No-P|**Sa|** `user_id` (UUID only), `venture_slug`, `rt`, `method`, HTTP status code, generic us-safe message.
M|No-P|tx|---
M|Rout|tx|```ts
M|Rout|expo|NextRequest) {
M|Rout|tx|const ventureSlug = req.headers.get('x-vt-slug') ?? 'unknown'
M|Rout|tx|try {
M|Rout|tx|// handler logic
M|Rout|tx|} catch (err) {
M|Rout|logE|'route_error', rt: '/ap/[rt]', method: 'POST', message: 'An unexpected er occurred.', venture_slug: ventureSlug })
M|Rout|retu|'An unexpected er occurred. Please try again.' }, { status: 500 })
M|Rout|tx|}
M|Rout|tx|}
M|Rout|tx|```
